administration (GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(3,289) = 2.77, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.04, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.017; drug: Ì†µÌªΩ = 0.003, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.57; Figure 4A). Second, we computed discrimination performance or Ì†µÌ±ë‚Ä≤ and found this measure was also not significantly different between vehicle and CNO administration (GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(7,82) = 40.7, Ì†µÌ±ù = 4.19 √ó 10=E\, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.757; drug: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.26, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.21; Figure 4B). Importantly, we observed a strong and significant correlation between discrimination accuracy Ì†µÌ±ë‚Ä≤ following CNO administration and following vehicle administration in rats with DREADDs expressed either in ACC (Pearson correlation; Ì†µÌ±ü = 0.847, Ì†µÌ±ù = 1.25 √ó 10=T) or BLA (Pearson correlation; Ì†µÌ±ü = 0.767, Ì†µÌ±ù = 1.21 √ó 10=>). Moreover, contrary to the significant effect of SNR on discrimination accuracy Ì†µÌ±ë‚Ä≤ (GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(7,82) = 40.7, Ì†µÌ±ù = 4.19 √ó 10=E\, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.757; ratio: Ì†µÌªΩ = 0.38, Ì†µÌ±ù = 2.38 √ó 10=MM), we found no significant main effect or interaction of drug condition (CNO vs. vehicle administration) and targeted brain region (ACC vs. BLA) on Ì†µÌ±ë‚Ä≤ (GLM; drug: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.26, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.21; region: Ì†µÌªΩ = 0.04, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.84), indicating that perceptual discrimination was not affected by ACC or BLA inhibition. Third, we found no significant effect of drug condition (CNO vs. vehicle) and targeted brain region on the decision criterion (i.e., the response bias; (Macmillan & Creelman, 1997); GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(3,86) = 1.62, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.19, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.02; drug: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.03, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.23; region: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.007, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.74). Finally, ACC and BLA inhibition failed to affect task engagement and perceptual processing speed as evidenced by the lack of change in the distributions of reaction time (GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(15,1742) = 234, Ì†µÌ±ù = 10=MT, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.665; drug: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.01, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.81; region: Ì†µÌªΩ = 0.001, Ì†µÌ±ù = 0.98; Figure 3F), and these responses also did not differ by trial type (correct vs. incorrect; Correct: GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(7,871) = 260, Ì†µÌ±ù = 2.01 √ó 10=ENV, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.674; ratio: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.33, Ì†µÌ±ù = 1.01 √ó 10=VM; Incorrect: GLM; Ì†µÌ∞π(7,871) = 236, Ì†µÌ±ù = 3.44 √ó 10=MQT, adjusted Ì†µÌ±ÖE = 0.652; ratio: Ì†µÌªΩ = ‚àí0.32, Ì†µÌ±ù = 3.14 √ó 10=?E; Figure 3G,H). This pattern also held for each value of contrast separately (Supplementary Figure 3D-F). Together these findings demonstrate that the observed effects of ACC and BLA inhibition on waiting times were not attributable to changes in decision-making processes related to visual discrimination.
